abstract: A remarkable level of discord enveloped the start of the nominating process as results from Iowa’s troubled caucuses showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders in a dead heat.
snippet: A remarkable level of discord enveloped the start of the nominating process as results from Iowa’s troubled caucuses showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders in a dead heat.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Democrats fought among themselves on Thursday over the troubled Iowa caucuses, even as near-final results showed Senator Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg in a dead heat for the lead.

abstract: Right now, the rewards of the economy are far too concentrated at the top.
snippet: Right now, the rewards of the economy are far too concentrated at the top.
lead_paragraph: Every Democrat running for president agrees that income inequality is one of the great problems of our time. And we all agree that the wealthy should pay more in taxes.

headline_main: Mike Bloomberg: Fixing Inequality Is My Priority

abstract: Michael Bloomberg has sworn off taking money from other people for his presidential campaign. But in private, he is courting rich Democrats, potentially posing a challenge for his moderate rivals.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg has sworn off taking money from other people for his presidential campaign. But in private, he is courting rich Democrats, potentially posing a challenge for his moderate rivals.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — In the middle of January, most Democratic presidential candidates were scrambling to raise money to keep their campaigns afloat. But at an airy gallery in downtown San Francisco, Michael R. Bloomberg gathered a group of several dozen local political donors to make a different kind of appeal.

abstract: Mayor de Blasio lays out a plan to ease New Yorkers’ anxiety about affordability and homelessness.
snippet: Mayor de Blasio lays out a plan to ease New Yorkers’ anxiety about affordability and homelessness.
lead_paragraph: A call to “Save Our City” might make more sense as a campaign slogan for a newcomer running for office in a city in steep decline, rather than a theme for a mayor in his seventh year in office, presiding over a booming New York.

headline_main: After Six Years in Office, New York’s Mayor Vows to ‘Save Our City’
headline_print_headline: De Blasio, After 6 Years  As the Mayor, Lays Out  Plans to ‘Save Our City’

abstract: And Michael Bloomberg and Bernie Sanders are competing fiercely in places like Fresno, where candidates very rarely go.
snippet: And Michael Bloomberg and Bernie Sanders are competing fiercely in places like Fresno, where candidates very rarely go.
lead_paragraph: FRESNO, Calif. — “There’s nothing magical about California,” Michael R. Bloomberg declared after a day flying through the state — or Iowa, for that matter, he added.

abstract: The Vermont senator’s announcement came as the Biden, Buttigieg and Warren campaigns are showing signs of financial strain.
snippet: The Vermont senator’s announcement came as the Biden, Buttigieg and Warren campaigns are showing signs of financial strain.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont raised $25 million in January, his campaign said on Thursday, a staggering sum that gives him an enviable financial advantage at a crucial moment in the Democratic primary race.
